{{Infobox person | name = Chris Boneau | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Birth-date and age|birth date†}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = Theatrical publicist | years_active = | known_for = Founder of Boneau/Bryan-Brown | notable_works = }}
'''Chris Boneau''' is a veteran theatrical [[publicist]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/broadway-pulled-resuscitate-york-city-sept-11-attacks-article-1.956976|title=Broadway pulled together to resuscitate New York City after Sept. 11 attacks|accessdate=26 December 2011|last=Dziemianowicz|first=Joe|publisher=[[New York Daily News]]|date=7 September 2011}}</ref>
Boneau formed [[Boneau/Bryan-Brown]], a partnership with [[Adrian Bryan-Brown]], in 1991. The company's credits include ''[[Angels in America]]'', ''[[Art (play)|Art]]'', ''[[Assassins (musical)|Assassins]]'', ''[[The Book of Mormon (musical)|The Book of Mormon]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2011/07/02/book-of-mormon-ticket-lottery/|title=Lottery-winning fans enraptured by special 'Book of Mormon' performance|accessdate=26 December 2011|last=Fetters|first=Ashley|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=2 July 2011|work=PopWatch}}</ref> ''[[The Boy from Oz]]'', ''[[Caroline, or Change]]'', ''[[The Color Purple (musical)|The Color Purple]]'', ''[[A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum]]'', ''[[Guys and Dolls]]'', ''[[Gypsy (musical)|Gypsy]]'', ''[[The Real Thing (play)|The Real Thing]]'', ''[[Spamalot]]'', ''[[Take Me Out (play)|Take Me Out]]'', ''[[Urinetown]]'', ''[[The Who's Tommy]]'', the [[Atlantic Theater Company]], [[Manhattan Theatre Club]], the [[Roundabout Theater Company]] and Walt [[Disney Theatrical Productions]].<ref name="american">{{Cite web|title=Biography - Chris Boneau|accessdate=26 December 2011|url=http://americantheatrewing.org/biography/detail/chris_boneau/|publisher=[[American Theatre Wing]]|date=August 2007|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531132904/http://americantheatrewing.org/biography/detail/chris_boneau/|archivedate=31 May 2012|df=}}</ref>
Mr. Boneau also serves on the Steering Committee for [[Broadway Cares/Equity Fights AIDS]], is an adjunct professor at [[Columbia University]]'s Oscar Hammerstein II Center for Theatre Studies and serves on the board of the Atlantic Theater Company.<ref name="american" />
