{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --> | name = Fahrettin Güneş | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = 1966 | death_date = | birth_place = [[Arpaçay-Kıraç]], [[Turkey]] | instrument = [[Vocals]] | genre = [[World music|World]] | occupation = [[Singer]] | years_active = 1985 to present day | label = | associated_acts = | website = | current_members = | past_members = }}
'''Fahrettin Güneş''' (born 1966) is a [[Germany|German]] singer, who is most notable for competing in the [[Türkvizyon Song Contest 2014]] with the song "Sevdiğim".
==Background==
In 1974 he moved to Germany. In 1990 at the age of 23 he opened his own studio in [[Düsseldorf]], [[Germany]], he has gone on to produce two albums from that studio, "Yandım, Tövbe ettim Sevmeye" (1994) and "Terekeme" (2006).<ref name=Biography>{{cite web|title=ALMANYA TEMSİLCİSİ: FAHRETTİN GÜNEŞ|url=http://turkvizyon.tv/yarismacilar/almanya-temsilcisi-fahrettin-gunes&44.html|website=Turkvizyon.tv|accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref> He currently performs at a number of events each year involving Turkic music.
==Türkvizyon Song Contest 2014== In 2014 Fahrettin Güneş was selected to represent Germany on their debut in the [[Türkvizyon Song Contest]]. Fahrettin represented Germany in Kazan, Tatarstan with the song "Sevdiğim", he was joined on stage by NART a [[Cologne]] based dance group.<ref name=Turkvizyon>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Germany: Fahrettin Güneş To Sing "Sevdiğim"|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/07/germany-fahrettin-gunes-to-sing-sevdigim/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref> He finished 21st in the semi final and did not qualify for the final.
